commentTextItems.html: the slower one, shorter in length, swatted to deep square-leg region. India push  New Zealand out of the tournament.

commentPostTextItems.html: Vettori: "When you win the toss here you want to put up a competitive total. The wickets gets easier when you have played yourself in; I found it that my self. Dhoni and Raina showed it as well. Some of our boys would be disappointed. It wasn't a bad fight back from us; we put them under some pressure. You can't expect to play on good decks all the time, when you come across deck like this you need to adapt."

Dhoni: "We wanted to get them out as cheap as possible. Nehra did well and then Yuvraj singh, our new find with the ball, did a good job. Sachin gave us a good start ... Raina also batted well with me. Every body was slightly tensed at the start of the game [as India are playing after a break]... the bowlers bowled really well. If there was one more spinner like Yuvi in their side, we would have been under more pressure. [on no 1] Frankly we are not thinking about it. We are just concentrating on what we do in the field. If we play good cricket, we eventually would be no 1 team in the world."

Man of the Match: Nehra : "I was struggling because of the injuries but I am back on track for the last 6-7 months. I wasn't too nervous today. I have been bowling well in the recent months and I just want to concentrate on line and length. The important thing was to pick up early wickets."
Stylish player of the day Tendulkar wins a bike.
That's it from us. Good bye and good luck.

dismissalComment.html: Umpire Dharmasena has sent Ryder on his way. Lbw. It landed full on the off and middle line and moved in to hit Ryder in front of the middle. Ryder was looking to play across the line and is a dead duck. It would have crashed into the leg stump.

headshotImage.caption: Ashish Nehra player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ashish Nehra player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Brendon McCullum lbw b Nehra 3 (9b 0x4 0x6 10m) SR: 33.33

dismissalComment.html: That's the 100th ODI wicket for Nehra. It landed on a length on the leg and middle and hit him in right in front of the middle. Plumb. And it appears as if it did hit the pad first too. What a comeback this is proving  for Nehra after years in wilderness.

headshotImage.caption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Ross Taylor c †Dhoni b Singh 11 (15b 2x4 0x6 15m) SR: 73.33

dismissalComment.html: NZ continue to wobble here. Taylor has been nicked out. It landed short of length and left Taylor who pushed at it; he did try to withdraw his bat at the last minute but it was too late by then. Edge and gone. Dhoni lunged to his right to collect that.

headshotImage.caption: Rahul Dravid player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Rahul Dravid player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Martin Guptill c Dravid b Yuvraj Singh 22 (42b 3x4 0x6 66m) SR: 52.38

dismissalComment.html: Yuvraj strikes in his first over. Fine catch by Rahul at first slip. It was pushed through around off stump, turned a touch and Guptill stabbed it low to left of Rahul who makes a sharp catch look very easy

headshotImage.caption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Grant Elliott c †Dhoni b Yuvraj Singh 22 (39b 0x4 0x6 66m) SR: 56.41

dismissalComment.html: quicker one, sliding down the leg side, Elliott misses the flick and Dhoni 'catches' it. Loud appeal and it has been given out. The first replay suggests it was off the pad. Will confirm again after more replays.

headshotImage.caption: Jacob Oram player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jacob Oram player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Jacob Oram player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jacob Oram player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Jacob Oram c & b Sharma 24 (45b 2x4 0x6 52m) SR: 53.33

dismissalComment.html: Done in by the slower one. It was around 114 kmph, on a length, Oram checked his shot and ended up chipping it straight back to Ishant

headshotImage.caption: Neil Broom player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Neil Broom player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Neil Broom player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Neil Broom player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Neil Broom c Raina b Yuvraj Singh 21 (28b 0x4 0x6 49m) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: and he has struck first up - this is a short innocuous delivery, asking to be hit, which Broom does, but straight and low to Raina at midwicket, who makes no mistake. Dismissals, they don't come softer

dismissalText.commentary: Kyle Mills b Singh 6 (20b 0x4 0x6 22m) SR: 30

dismissalComment.html: No 8. It was a short-of-length delivery moving away from Mills who tried to punch it through the off side but ended up dragging it back to his stumps. It can happen on a slow track such as this. Gary Kirsten applauds from the dressing room.

dismissalText.commentary: Daniel Vettori b Sharma 25 (36b 1x4 0x6 66m) SR: 69.44

dismissalComment.html: Clatter! It landed back of a length around off and middle line and shaped in a touch, Vettori went for an on-the-up drive but pushed his bat outside the line and was beaten as the delivery moved in a touch.

headshotImage.longCaption: Harbhajan Singh player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Ian Butler c Harbhajan Singh b Nehra 6 (31b 0x4 0x6 41m) SR: 19.35

dismissalComment.html: India need 156 to win. It was the bouncer, Butler tries to upper cut it to third man but succeeds in lobbing a dolly to cover!

headshotImage.longCaption: Dinesh Karthik player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Dinesh Karthik player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dinesh Karthik player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Dinesh Karthik lbw b Mills 4 (11b 0x4 0x6 8m) SR: 36.36

dismissalComment.html: Got him! It landed on a length just outside off and moved in to hit him on the middle and leg line. It would have missed the leg stump but that's that. New Zealand taste some early success.

dismissalText.commentary: Sachin Tendulkar c Guptill b Vettori 46 (55b 6x4 0x6 81m) SR: 83.63

dismissalComment.html: Oh my ... what a soft dismissal! The ball stopped a touch on Tendulkar who was on the back foot and he ended up chipping it straight to cover. Tame way to get out. Vettori can't believe his luck.

dismissalText.commentary: Rahul Dravid lbw b Oram 14 (45b 1x4 0x6 65m) SR: 31.11

dismissalComment.html: trapped in front. Fullish, straight on the middle and leg line, Dravid shuffled across to flick it across the line, misses and it would have crashed into the leg stump. Dharmasena makes the correct decision.

dismissalText.commentary: Yuvraj Singh c Guptill b Vettori 8 (13b 2x4 0x6 22m) SR: 61.53

dismissalComment.html: Dan the man strikes. He flighted this one outside off, slowed up the pace and got it to drift away, Yuvraj tried to repeat his slog sweep but only skied the ball to midwicket. Lovely clever bowling this
